The paper deals with decidability of a logical system (Propositional Dynamic Logic) on forests, which suggests it belongs to the Logic (cs.LO) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. The paper also uses algebraic structures (forest algebras) to characterize the logical system, which could place it in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The paper's approach to solving the problem involves a distributive law, which could place it in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper's results have implications for decision-making in artificial intelligence, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
